  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "If someone is caught laundering money, they can face serious legal consequences, including:\n\n1. Criminal Charges\n- Potential federal or state prosecution\n- Money laundering is a felony offense\n- Possible prison sentence (usually 5-20 years)\n- Significant financial penalties/fines\n\n2. Financial Penalties\n- Seizure of assets involved in laundering\n- Large monetary fines\n- Potential civil asset forfeiture\n\n3. Professional Consequences\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty finding future employment\n- Criminal record impacting career opportunities\n\n4. Additional Legal Actions\n- Potential additional charges like tax evasion\n- Civil lawsuits\n- Required restitution\n\nThe specific consequences depend on the amount of money involved, jurisdiction, and specific circumstances of the case.",
